 Lorraine Valentine suffers from the rare disease erythropoietic protoporphyria -LRB- EPP which causes her skin to burn and become unbearable itchy when she is exposed to sunlight or UV light .
A holiday abroad left the 42-year-old in hospital for six days as the heat caused her entire body to swell .
Her sun allergy means she has to keep herself completely covered , as even a small dose of sun on her skin leaves her in pain .
Miss Valentine is in a drug that can help her .